課程學習目標 Course Objectives
This course introduces computational tools, Introduction to environmental processes and their simulation (reaction)Introduction to environmental processes and their simulation (transportation)Introduction to computational tools for differential equation modelsPrinciples of optimization and parameter estimation Part I is taught by Prof. Wen-Che Whou, and other parts are taught 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction to the course items/Part 1: Reaction (I)2Part I: Reaction (II)3Part I: Reaction (III)4Part I: Reaction (IV)5Part I: Reaction (V)6Part I: Reaction (VI)7Part II: Introduction to computational tools (I)8Part II: Transportation (I)9Part II: Transportation (II)10Part II: Transportation (III)11Part II: Transportation (IV)12Part II: Transportation (V)13Part III: Numerical methods for differential equation models (I)14Part III: Numerical methods for differential equation models (II)15Part IV: Optimization and parameter estimation16Part IV: Optimization and parameter estimation17Part IV: Optimization and parameter estimation18Part IV: Optimization and parameter estimation 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


