課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    This course introduces computational tools, e.g., MATLAB and VBA, and basic concepts of environmental modeling with numerical methods. Two important mathematical principles used in environmental engineering and system analysis, i.e. optimization and simulation, will be emphasized. The course is separated into 4 parts:
Introduction to environmental processes and their simulation (reaction)
Introduction to environmental processes and their simulation (transportation)
Introduction to computational tools for differential equation models
Principles of optimization and parameter estimation 
Part I is taught by Prof. Wen-Che Whou, and other parts are taught by Prof. Chih-Hua Chang.    

